description:
&lt;p&gt;Interested in working for a NHS Trust that is in the Top 20% of similar hospitals for excellent Staff engagement? An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic individual with housing management experience to join our Accommodation Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About the role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for the allocation and control of residences at The Royal Bournemouth Hospital, together with any offsite properties. Working closely with other teams, you will be responsible for the high standard of Customer Service that is responsive to the Trust&#39;s needs acting as a key point of liaison with residents regarding any matters of concern, complaints or suggestions. You will proactively manage potential breaches of tenure as well as monitor rent accounts and work with the relevant teams in Medical Staffing Personnel, Housekeeping and the senior Building Officer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an adaptable person who thrives in a fast paced environment, where no two days are the same. The ideal candidate will have worked in a similar role and have a working knowledge of the 1980 Housing Act with an understanding of the amendments in relation to accommodation for doctors in training. They will be able to demonstrate relevant experience in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handling conflict, difficult conversations and negotiations professionally and persuasively with customers either face-to-face, by phone or online, including those who may be in difficult and/or emotionally charged situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clear and concise letters with a business level of written fluency on complex issues to customers and managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidently use Microsoft Office and other ICT systems to input, retrieve, interrogate and present financial, performance and other data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
